1
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:16,200
Burma Road.

2
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,440
Then why are you here?

3
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,160
Maybe it's destiny

4
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:23,890
that gave you a new mission.

5
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,360
Mission?

6
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:39,880
New China.

7
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:41,800
We won.

8
00:01:42,759 --> 00:01:43,640
We really won.

9
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:47,240
Our victory was just a matter of time.

10
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,289
A matter of time.

11
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:51,600
But back then,

12
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,759
we had no idea when we would win.

13
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:03,160
If I do the math,

14
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,530
he must be over a hundred years old now.

15
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,760
Then we really hit the jackpot.

16
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:13,760
And Japan surrendered 80 years ago.

17
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:19,960
Those bastards finally surrendered.

18
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,440
But why

19
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:28,880
am I here?

20
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:32,960
Guys,

21
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:35,000
I know it's inappropriate timing,

22
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:39,200
but can we go get some food first?

23
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,200
I've found a lot of good food nearby.

24
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,440
Should we go try it?

25
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,840
Let's take you to see New China.

26
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:46,440
Let's go.

27
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:56,980
It's so late, but there are still so many people.

28
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,480
Such a lively atmosphere.

29
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,160
This is so bustling.

30
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,720
This is a midnight snack, night market,

31
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,880
you know?

32
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:05,480
The nightlife for young people

33
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:06,880
hasn't even started yet.

34
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,680
Youlv Courtyard.

35
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,920
This place is nice, Yiyi.

36
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:22,880
Of course.

37
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,640
Look who booked it.

38
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,240
The vibe is great.

39
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,320
Good taste, Yiyi.

40
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:33,579
Have a seat. Let's have a good meal today.

41
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:37,079
Order whatever you want.

42
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,210
It's my treat today.

43
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:41,320
Mr. Zhang is so generous tonight.

44
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,079
It's all to welcome the newcomer.

45
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:44,680
I had this in Nanyang before.

46
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,320
Let me open it for you.

47
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:56,440
How could you have had Cola?

48
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,700
This is a modern drink.

49
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,440
Cola has been around since 1886.

50
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,920
It already existed in his time.

51
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:03,040
How do you know?

52
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,040
Just ask AI.

53
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:07,120
But no matter how powerful AI is,

54
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:09,720
it can't compare to his personal experiences.

55
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,680
Alright, let's order first.

56
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,490
See what you want to eat.

57
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:28,800
Roast chicken.

58
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:31,040
Roast chicken is the specialty here.

59
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,730
The most expensive one.

60
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:39,159
You're good at ordering.

61
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:44,080
The words on this

62
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,840
are so weird.

63
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,460
I don't recognize them at all.

64
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:51,520
Are you illiterate or uneducated?

65
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,890
Of course I'm educated.

66
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,760
Grandpa taught me how to read since I was little.

67
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,640
I have no problem reading books and newspapers.

68
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:00,080
You're just bragging.

69
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:02,010
Oh, it's not that he's illiterate,

70
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:05,320
it's just that he can't read simplified Chinese characters.

71
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,640
I almost forgot.

72
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,900
You are an antique from the last century.

73
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:12,200
Very few people were literate in old China.

74
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:14,880
After the founding of New China, to eliminate illiteracy,

75
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:16,080
traditional characters were simplified

76
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,080
and simplified Chinese was introduced.

77
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,280
Simplified Chinese?

78
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:25,480
Alright, stop the lecture.

79
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,740
Let me do the ordering.

80
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,720
Wait until you finish explaining to him.

81
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,880
I'm starving.

82
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,680
What do you want to eat? Any dietary restrictions?

83
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,880
Do you eat spicy food?

84
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,600
I told you to drink less cola.

85
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,200
Will you be able to eat later?

86
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,720
Waiter.

87
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,240
Order.

88
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,050
This is good.

89
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,320
This one is okay too.

90
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,200
Drink less.

91
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,600
I ordered a lot of dishes.

92
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,520
You won't be able to eat later.

93
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,200
This tastes good.

94
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,520
Sweet and sour.

95
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,080
Yeah.

96
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:11,000
Boss, is number 246 ready?

97
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,020
This is not bad.

98
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,820
I think this is delicious too.

99
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,160
Hey, little sister.

100
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,640
What's up? Miss me?

101
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,560
Not busy, not busy.

102
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,010
Waiting for my food.

103
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,760
Another 88,000?

104
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:33,800
What?

105
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,520
Three golds turned into five golds?

106
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,560
Discuss it with your mom.

107
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:42,280
Let's talk about this after we get married.

108
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,280
Lili.

109
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:50,040
What does her marriage have to do with us?

110
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:50,840
She wants what she wants.

111
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,240
We live our lives.

112
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:54,760
What?

113
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,540
If we don't have it, we won't get married.

114
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:03,280
Why do we have to compare our marriage with others?

115
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,720
I grew up herding cattle and sheep in the mountains.

116
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,250
Finally made it to the city.

117
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,960
Do you know how many jobs I work a day?

118
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,960
I've never seen a thick stack of money.

119
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:35,520
Boss, is number 246 ready?

120
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,760
Xiao Pumao.

121
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,480
Yaozu, what does she mean by Xiao Pumao?

122
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,480
Is she calling me?

123
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,680
In Dai culture, Xiao Pumao means young man.

124
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,640
Xiao Pushao means young girl.

125
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:10,370
The Water Splashing Festival is the Dai New Year.

126
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,480
Xiao Pushao.

127
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,440
These are candies from Nanyang.

128
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,930
They are very sweet.

129
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:29,640
Grandma says I can't take things from outsiders.

130
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:34,760
Since coming back, I'm half a local.

131
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,039
Things from a local,

132
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,299
you can accept, right?

133
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:43,080
Besides, it's New Year.

134
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,960
We should

135
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,280
eat candy and be happy.

136
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,000
Yaozu, save me.

137
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,560
What are you giggling about?

138
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,600
Azu, I realize

139
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,040
I have fallen for her.

140
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:24,640
Who? Xiao Pushao?

141
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:25,680
Yeah.

142
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,640
What, love at first sight?

143
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:32,640
It keeps echoing in my mind,

144
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,560
her calling me Xiao Pumao.

145
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:35,800
Xiao Pumao.

146
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:37,760
Azu,

147
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:40,560
should I marry her?

148
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,410
Grandma will definitely like her.

149
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:47,920
Then grandma can teach her a lot.

150
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:53,200
Aren't you afraid grandma will tell her about your sleepwalking,

151
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,130
teeth grinding,

152
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:58,160
and snoring habits?

153
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:00,960
No way. She's my grandma.

154
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,520
Well, maybe I will.

155
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,200
I'll tell her that you

156
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,540
are afraid of the dark,

157
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,260
and dare not walk at night.

158
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,120
Nonsense.

159
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:13,480
I'm a man. How could I be scared?

160
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:19,680
My stomach hasn't stopped rumbling since we got back.

161
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,000
No, I need to find a place.

162
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,440
Zu,

163
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:26,920
do you want to go with me?

164
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,600
See? What did I just say?

165
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,520
You're a grown man.

166
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:33,200
You still need someone to accompany you to poop.

167
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,060
Go by yourself.

168
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,920
I can't hold it. Don't leave.

169
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:36,520
Wait for me here.

170
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:38,320
Otherwise, I'll call your name.

171
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,120
Zu,

172
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:03,720
are you still there?

173
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,320
Zu!

174
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,520
Zu, are you still there?

175
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,400
No.

176
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:23,680
Zu, help me!
